        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">Business Car Finance Structures</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">When purchasing a vehicle for business use in Australia, the finance structure you choose has significant implications for tax, cash flow, GST, and asset ownership. There are four main structures:</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Chattel Mortgage (Most Popular for ABN Holders)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">You own the vehicle from day one. The lender holds a mortgage over it until paid off. Claim GST on purchase upfront, deduct interest, and depreciate the vehicle. For a $60,000 ute used 100% for business, the GST claim alone is approximately $5,454 in your next BAS. Best for: ABN holders, sole traders, partnerships, companies, and trusts that use the vehicle predominantly for business.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Commercial Hire Purchase</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The lender owns the vehicle and hires it to you. Ownership transfers on the final payment. You can claim interest and depreciation but GST treatment differs from chattel mortgage. Similar to chattel mortgage in practice but suits some structures better.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Finance Lease</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">The lender owns the vehicle throughout. You return it or pay the residual at the end. Running costs are your responsibility. GST is claimed progressively on lease payments rather than upfront. Best for: businesses that prefer off-balance-sheet financing or regularly turn over vehicles.</p>
        <h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-xl text-[#0d4d3e] mt-8 mb-4">Novated Lease (Employees Only)</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">If the vehicle is part of a salary package, a novated lease provides income tax savings through salary sacrifice. FBT applies to petrol/diesel vehicles; battery EVs are FBT-exempt. Best for: employees with supportive employers.</p>
        </section>
